<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="479" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,968,2039]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1076,1102]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Etymology.</emphasis>
From 
<emphasis box="[411,534,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">adiastaltos</emphasis>
Gr., meaning not clearly defined, indefinite, referring to the inconspicuous features of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="479" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,968,2039]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,479,1148,1174]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
Description (
<typeStatus box="[353,467,1148,1174]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Holotype</typeStatus>
).
</emphasis>
Shell conical, straight, reaching about 
<quantity box="[918,1004,1148,1175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1075,1161,1148,1175]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
wide. Larval shell whitish, conical, with 2.75 convex whorls, 
<quantity box="[583,670,1184,1211]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="330.0">330 µm</quantity>
wide, 
<quantity box="[745,832,1184,1211]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="380.0">380 µm</quantity>
in height; smooth, transition to teleoconch marked by distinct incremental scar. Teleoconch with about 5.5 whorls, convex outline; suture well demarcated, sloping; subsutural zone indistinct; surface smooth, incremental scars well demarcated, appearing at intervals of about 0.7 whorl. Last whorl about 50% of the shell length; base rounded. Aperture short, pear shaped, acute posteriorly and rounded anteriorly; outer lip thin, opisthocline, sinuous, slightly retracting near the suture and slightly projecting in the uppermost third; inner lip sinuous, sloping, reflected and well demarcated. Not umbilicate. Shell vitreous, colorless.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,968,2039]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1400,1426]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Measurements.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[388,492,1400,1426]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Holotype</typeStatus>
MNRJ 35250†, 8 whorls, SL= 
<quantity box="[841,929,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
; BWL= 
<quantity box="[1024,1112,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
; AL= 
<quantity box="[1181,1269,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
; SW= 
<quantity box="[1344,1432,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
; AW= 
<quantity box="[218,307,1436,1463]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="480" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,968,2039]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1472,1498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros, 2021" authorityName="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2021" box="[322,554,1472,1498]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adiastalta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,554,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Melanella adiastalta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[560,650,1472,1498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[560,650,1472,1498]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
at first has inconspicuous features but can be distinguished from other similar species occurring in deep waters of the Atlantic. Despite the presence of only a single shell, we describe 
<taxonomicName authority="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros, 2021" authorityName="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2021" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adiastalta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. adiastalta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[271,361,1544,1570]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[271,361,1544,1570]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
based on the combination of consistent shell features that enable us to discriminate this species from remaining eulimids.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,968,2039]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<taxonomicName authority="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros, 2021" authorityName="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2021" box="[199,418,1616,1642]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adiastalta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,418,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Melanella adiastalta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[424,508,1616,1642]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[424,508,1616,1642]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Watson" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[791,900,1617,1642]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sarissa">
<emphasis box="[791,900,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. sarissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[913,1015,1616,1642]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-25@24.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. A–L. Melanella sarissa (Watson, 1883):A, B. Holotype of Eulima sarissa Watson, 1883, NHMUK 1887.2.9.1599; C. NMW 1955.158.26254. D, L. Syntype of Melanella cinca Dall, 1927, USNM 108028. E. MNRJ 28845. F–K. IBUFRJ 19708. J. Detail of protoconch, frontal view; arrow indicates transition protoconch-teleoconch. K, L. Detail of protoconch, apical view; arrow indicates transition protoconch-teleoconch. Scale bars: A–G= 1.0 mm; H, I= 200 µm; J= 100 µm; K= 50 µm; L= 75 µm. Credits: A, B, courtesy of NHMUK; C, courtesy of NMW; D, L, courtesy of USNM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542957/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Figure 12</figureCitation>
A–K) because it has more convex teleoconch whorls, a wider spire angle (26° 
<emphasis box="[568,597,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">vs.</emphasis>
22° in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Watson" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[675,785,1653,1678]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sarissa">
<emphasis box="[675,785,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. sarissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and a smaller number of protoconch whorls (2.75 
<emphasis box="[1334,1363,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">vs.</emphasis>
4.0).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,968,2039]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<taxonomicName authority="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros, 2021" authorityName="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2021" box="[199,432,1688,1714]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adiastalta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,432,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Melanella adiastalta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[439,529,1688,1714]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[439,529,1688,1714]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Bouchet &amp; Waren, 1986" authorityName="Bouchet &amp; Waren" authorityYear="1986" box="[834,1257,1688,1714]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="insculpta">
<emphasis box="[834,975,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. insculpta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A." box="[982,1257,1688,1714]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" pagination="299 - 576" refId="ref32770" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1986) Revision of the northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Aclididae, Eulimidae, Epitoniidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico, Supplemento 2, 299 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 140762" type="journal article" year="1986">Bouchet &amp; Warén, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the North Atlantic, by the faster increase in diameter of the spire. Both species reach about 8.5 whorls, but 
<taxonomicName authority="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros, 2021" authorityName="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2021" box="[1245,1395,1724,1750]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adiastalta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1245,1395,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. adiastalta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="28" pageNumber="479" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has 
<quantity box="[249,334,1760,1787]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
wide while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bouchet &amp; Waren" authorityYear="1986" box="[467,606,1760,1786]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="insculpta">
<emphasis box="[467,606,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. insculpta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 
<quantity box="[655,740,1760,1787]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
wide (
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A." box="[813,1134,1760,1787]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" pagination="299 - 576" refId="ref32770" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1986) Revision of the northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Aclididae, Eulimidae, Epitoniidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico, Supplemento 2, 299 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 140762" type="journal article" year="1986">Bouchet &amp; Warén 1986: 376</bibRefCitation>
). Additionally, the outer lip of 
<taxonomicName authority="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros, 2021" authorityName="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2021" box="[181,329,1796,1822]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adiastalta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[181,329,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. adiastalta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[335,424,1796,1822]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[335,424,1796,1822]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
protrudes gradually (
<figureCitation box="[661,788,1796,1823]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1614,1638]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-102@29.[151,1435,381,1590]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 15. A–G. Melanella adiastalta sp. nov.: holotype, MNRJ 35250. F. Detail of protoconch, frontal view. G. Detail of protoconch, apical view. Scale bars: A–C= 1.0 mm; D, E= 200 µm; F, G= 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542965/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Figure 15E</figureCitation>
) while it is more accentuated in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bouchet &amp; Waren" authorityYear="1986" box="[1147,1286,1796,1822]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="insculpta">
<emphasis box="[1147,1286,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. insculpta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A." pageId="28" pageNumber="479" pagination="299 - 576" refId="ref32770" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1986) Revision of the northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Aclididae, Eulimidae, Epitoniidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico, Supplemento 2, 299 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 140762" type="journal article" year="1986">Bouchet &amp; Warén 1986</bibRefCitation>
: figs. 885, 887).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,968,2039]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<taxonomicName authority="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros, 2021" authorityName="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2021" box="[199,436,1868,1894]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adiastalta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,436,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Melanella adiastalta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[447,540,1868,1894]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[447,540,1868,1894]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jordan" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[700,903,1868,1894]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="martynjordani">
<emphasis box="[700,903,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. martynjordani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Jordan, H. K." box="[921,1075,1868,1895]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" pagination="264 - 269" refId="ref34436" refString="Jordan, H. K. (1895) On some new species of British Mollusca. Proceedings of the Malacological Society of London, 1, 264 - 269. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / oxfordjournals. mollus. a 064131" type="journal article" year="1895">
<collectingCountry box="[921,1000,1868,1894]" name="Jordan" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Jordan</collectingCountry>
, 1895
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Bouchet &amp; Waren, 1986" authorityName="Bouchet &amp; Waren" authorityYear="1986" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="obtusoapicata">
<emphasis box="[1099,1299,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. obtusoapicata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A." pageId="28" pageNumber="479" pagination="299 - 576" refId="ref32770" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1986) Revision of the northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Aclididae, Eulimidae, Epitoniidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico, Supplemento 2, 299 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 140762" type="journal article" year="1986">Bouchet &amp; Warén, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dautzenberg &amp; Fischer, 1912)" baseAuthorityName="Dautzenberg &amp; Fischer" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[307,852,1904,1930]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pseudoglabra">
<emphasis box="[307,498,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. pseudoglabra</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dautzenberg, P. &amp; Fischer, H." box="[512,844,1904,1930]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" pagination="1 - 629" refId="ref33504" refString="Dautzenberg, P. &amp; Fischer, H. (1912) Mollusques provenant des campagnes de l' Hirondelle et de la Princesse-Alice dans les mers du Nord. Resultats des Campagnes Scientifiques Accomplies sur son Yacht par Albert Ier Prince Souverain de Monaco, 37, 1 - 629. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 61117" type="journal article" year="1912">Dautzenberg &amp; Fischer, 1912</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
