<taxonomicName authority="Bouchet &amp; Waren, 1986" authorityName="Bouchet &amp; Waren" authorityYear="1986" box="[906,1296,1904,1930]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turrita">
<emphasis box="[906,1016,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. turrita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A." box="[1023,1296,1904,1930]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" pagination="299 - 576" refId="ref32770" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1986) Revision of the northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Aclididae, Eulimidae, Epitoniidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico, Supplemento 2, 299 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 140762" type="journal article" year="1986">Bouchet &amp; Warén, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, all from the Northeast Atlantic area, mainly by the more convex teleoconch whorls (
<figureCitation box="[950,1114,1940,1967]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1614,1638]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-102@29.[151,1435,381,1590]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 15. A–G. Melanella adiastalta sp. nov.: holotype, MNRJ 35250. F. Detail of protoconch, frontal view. G. Detail of protoconch, apical view. Scale bars: A–C= 1.0 mm; D, E= 200 µm; F, G= 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542965/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Figure 15A, B</figureCitation>
). Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName authority="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros, 2021" authorityName="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2021" box="[1287,1436,1940,1966]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adiastalta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1287,1436,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. adiastalta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,241,1976,2002]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,241,1976,2002]" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a more protruding outer lip (
<figureCitation box="[613,742,1976,2003]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1614,1638]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-102@29.[151,1435,381,1590]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 15. A–G. Melanella adiastalta sp. nov.: holotype, MNRJ 35250. F. Detail of protoconch, frontal view. G. Detail of protoconch, apical view. Scale bars: A–C= 1.0 mm; D, E= 200 µm; F, G= 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542965/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Figure 15E</figureCitation>
) than 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jordan" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[813,1012,1976,2002]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="martynjordani">
<emphasis box="[813,1012,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. martynjordani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a higher number of whorls in the protoconch (
<figureCitation box="[292,423,2012,2039]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1614,1638]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-102@29.[151,1435,381,1590]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 15. A–G. Melanella adiastalta sp. nov.: holotype, MNRJ 35250. F. Detail of protoconch, frontal view. G. Detail of protoconch, apical view. Scale bars: A–C= 1.0 mm; D, E= 200 µm; F, G= 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542965/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">Figure 15G</figureCitation>
) than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bouchet &amp; Waren" authorityYear="1986" box="[493,604,2013,2038]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="28" pageNumber="479" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="turrita">
<emphasis box="[493,604,2013,2038]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">M. turrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(2.75 
<emphasis box="[676,707,2013,2038]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="479">vs.</emphasis>
1.5).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">
<taxonomicName authority="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros, 2021" authorityName="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2021" box="[199,434,151,177]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adiastalta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,434,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">Melanella adiastalta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[442,534,151,177]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[442,534,151,177]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Bouchet &amp; Waren, 1986" authorityName="Bouchet &amp; Waren" authorityYear="1986" box="[663,1144,151,177]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Eulima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="anonyma">
<emphasis box="[663,856,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">Eulima anonyma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A." box="[864,1144,151,177]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" pagination="299 - 576" refId="ref32770" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1986) Revision of the northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Aclididae, Eulimidae, Epitoniidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico, Supplemento 2, 299 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 140762" type="journal article" year="1986">Bouchet &amp; Warén, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from off 
<collectingCountry box="[1261,1359,151,177]" name="Portugal" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, in the number and shape of protoconch whorls, but the protoconch is shorter (380 μm high 
<emphasis box="[1085,1115,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">vs.</emphasis>
500 μm high in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bouchet &amp; Waren" authorityYear="1986" box="[1294,1427,187,212]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Eulima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="anonyma">
<emphasis box="[1294,1427,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">E. anonyma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A." box="[159,493,223,250]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" pagination="299 - 576" refId="ref32770" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1986) Revision of the northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Aclididae, Eulimidae, Epitoniidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico, Supplemento 2, 299 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 140762" type="journal article" year="1986">Bouchet &amp; Warén 1986: 467</bibRefCitation>
). Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName authority="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros, 2021" authorityName="Souza &amp; Pimenta &amp; Barros" authorityYear="2021" box="[670,821,223,249]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Melanella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="adiastalta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[670,821,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">M. adiastalta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[830,921,223,249]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[830,921,223,249]" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a wider shell, despite reaching a smaller number of whorls (8 whorls, SW= 
<quantity box="[543,629,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
<emphasis box="[635,666,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="480">vs.</emphasis>
10 whorls, SW= 
<quantity box="[862,952,259,285]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="29" pageNumber="480" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
